  "text": "GA is one of the most efficient and popular techniques that are used to find the optimal or near-optimal solution for hard problems with a large search space particularity in combinatorial problems where the search space is of factorial order. The primary function of GA is to generate and manipulate several individuals using suitable genetic operators to find the solutions. Thus, GA is classified as one of global search techniques that depend on the principle of collecting solutions instead of adopting a single solution [CITATION_1] . Generally, the computation time that classical GA needs to reach the optimal solution is large. However, it can be rectified by using heuristics in specific way. Applying heuristics may decrease the computation time and improve the solutions evolved by GAs [CITATION_2] .",
